2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a learning-based approach to solve the problem. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible sub-category as the paper deals with intelligent selection of images based on object class. 
4. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with natural language processing in the form of bag-of-words representation of images. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible sub-category as the paper deals with multiple image collections.
